[In the SV `P/BPAssignOp` verifiers](https://github.com/llvm/circt/blob/main/lib/Dialect/SV/SVOps.cpp#L1142-L1156) it is assumed that the target argument is defined by an op (`isa` used on `getDefiningOp`). Hence, in the case of a `hw.inout` input port, the verifier crashes.

i.e.:
```mlir
hw.module @unsupported(%a: !hw.inout<i42>) {
  %clock = hw.constant 1 : i1
  %c42 = hw.constant 42 : i42
  sv.alwaysff(posedge %clock) {
    sv.passign %a, %c42 : i42
  }
}
```
